{"questionId":"20890","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A large school has students from Year 6 to Year 12.</p>\n<p>A group of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn></math> students in Year 12 were randomly selected and surveyed to find out how&nbsp;many hours per week they each spend doing homework. Their results are represented by&nbsp;the following cumulative frequency graph.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/a6dbe6a979943ec1273dad19153ad622e904e2d3.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This same information is represented by the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7ec8a1baf1c50e1d6505353e47c32341ff3bb7f6.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>There are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>320</mn></math> students in Year 12 at this school.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Estimate the number of Year 12 students that spend more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn></math> hours each week&nbsp;doing homework.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math> of the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn></math> students OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math> spend more than <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>15</mn></math> hours doing homework&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mn>80</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mn>320</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>320</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>20</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp;(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn></math>&nbsp;(students)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"20890","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.7d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Estimate the number of Year 12 students that spend more than 15 hours each week doing homework.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.2—Histograms, CF graphs, box plots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}